        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:88:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/88/5437",
        "text": [
          " : \"أَوَّلُ شَيْءٍ يُبْدَأُ بِهِ مِنَ اَلْمَالِ اَلْكَفَنُ ثُمَّ اَلدَّيْنُ ثُمَّ اَلْوَصِيَّةُ ثُمَّ اَلْمِيرَاثُ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5437 - Al-Sakuni narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"The first thing to be taken care of from the wealth (of the deceased) is the shroud (for burial), then the debts, then the will, and then the inheritance.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2435,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
