        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:88:5",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/88/5441",
        "text": [
          " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ مَاتَ وَ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ بِقَدْرِ ثَمَنِ كَفَنِهِ قَالَ \"يُجْعَلُ مَا تَرَكَ فِي ثَمَنِ كَفَنِهِ إِلاَّ أَنْ يَتَّجِرَ عَلَيْهِ بَعْضُ اَلنَّاسِ فَيُكَفِّنُونَهُ وَ يُقْضَى مَا عَلَيْهِ مِمَّا تَرَكَ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5441 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Ali ibn Riʾab from Zurarah, who said:\nI asked Imam (as) about a man who died while owing a debt equal to the price of his shroud.\nImam (as) said: \"What he left behind should be used for the price of his shroud unless some people choose to contribute and provide his shroud. In that case, his debt should be paid off from what he left behind.\""
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
